Discover 3 local security incidents

In this activity, I researched several cybersecurity incidents that occurred in Australia to understand how security issues affect real systems and people.

1. Latitude Financial data breach
Latitude Financial experienced a data breach where attackers accessed and stole personal information, including identification documents. This incident shows how financial institutions are targeted and how sensitive data can be exposed.
https://www.latitudefinancial.com.au/latitude-cyber-incident/

2. NSW Clubs ransomware attack  
Several clubs in New South Wales were affected by ransomware attacks, where systems were locked and data was disrupted. This shows how ransomware can impact business operations and cause financial loss.

3. UWA cyber incident (August 2025)  
The University of Western Australia experienced a cyber incident in August 2025 involving unauthorised access to systems. This raised concerns about the security of student and staff data. It highlights the importance of protecting university systems and responding quickly to potential breaches.
https://www.abc.net.au/news/2025-08-11/university-of-western-australia-uwa-suffers-major-data-breach/105636074

Overall, these incidents demonstrate that cybersecurity threats are common in Australia and can affect different types of organisations, including financial services, businesses, and educational institutions.
